    {
      "id": "f61c57b6_6d221d25",
      "file_path": "participant/participant-impl/participant-impl-policy/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/acm/participant/policy/client/HttpClientTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 13,
      "line": 75,
      "message": "Yes, the test createBadPolicy is creating an empty ToscaServiceTemplate object with null values on all the fields. When the apiClient business logic serializes it with gson before, it was omiting the null fields and produced {\"name\":\"NULL\",\"version\":\"0.0.0\"} whose request body size was less than 40. \n\nWhen jackson is used for serialization, it produces the following output including all the null fields.\n{\"name\":\"NULL\",\"version\":\"0.0.0\",\"metadata\":null,\"description\":null,\"type\":null,\"typeVersion\":null,\"definedName\":null,\"definedVersion\":null,\"derived_from\":null,\"tosca_definitions_version\":null,\"data_types\":null,\"capability_types\":null,\"node_types\":null,\"relationship_types\":null,\"policy_types\":null,\"topology_template\":null}\n\nhence I had to adjust the condition here for the mockserver response.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6070,
        "name": "Ramesh Murugan Iyer",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramesh.murugan.iyer@est.tech",
        "username": "rameshiyer27"
      },
      "updated": "2026-02-09 16:30:12.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "cdd66243_c55cefbd",
      "unresolved": true
    },
